69
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:08,240
So, this was very well done coverage.

70
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:11,380
It's very unusual because if you look at

71
00:04:11,380 --> 00:04:16,180
the media coverage most of the medical
literature you'll see that they

72
00:04:16,180 --> 00:04:19,160
almost always talk about relative risks
and not, and not absolute risks.

73
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:21,360
And that's not really the, the fault of
the media necessarily.

74
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:24,988
That's just the way that these data are
usually presented in medical studies.

75
00:04:24,988 --> 00:04:30,150
So just to, to drill down a little bit
more on,

76
00:04:30,150 --> 00:04:32,550
on the data from this study, so if you
looked at breast cancer,

77
00:04:32,550 --> 00:04:36,320
you can see that the rate of breast cancer
