91
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:22,670
It's not that the number is wrong, it's,
that's the true increase in relative risk.

92
00:05:22,670 --> 00:05:26,120
But, if you look at the absolute risk
numbers, you can see that the risk to

93
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:28,640
any individual woman is actually really,
really small.

94
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:33,340
Imagine if a woman hears that she has a
26% increased risk of breast cancer,

95
00:05:33,340 --> 00:05:35,160
that sounds very impressive and scary.

96
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:41,670
But in fact, her increase or absolute
increase in risk is just 0.08% per year.

97
00:05:41,670 --> 00:05:45,740
So eight out of 10,000 is 0.08%, so it's
actually a very,

98
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:50,020
very small increase in risk in, for any
particular, one particular woman.

99
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:53,390
You can see how different the message
looks depending on

100
00:05:53,390 --> 00:05:55,630
whether you give the relative risk versus
